      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the wet ingredients",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 150°C fan. Butter and line the square tin. Melt the {{unsalted-butter}}, {{black-treacle}}, {{golden-syrup}}, and {{dark-brown-sugar}} together in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth. Do not let it boil. Remove from the heat and stir in the {{whole-milk}} and beaten {{eggs}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In a large bowl, combine the {{rolled-oats}}, {{plain-flour}}, {{ginger-ground}}, {{mixed-spice}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Pour the warm treacle mixture over the dry ingredients and stir to combine. The batter will be loose and dark.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 42 to 45 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour into the tin. Bake for 42 to 45 minutes. The top will feel just firm when pressed and a skewer will come out with a few moist crumbs attached. The cake will look slightly underset but will firm as it cools. Leave in the tin until completely cold, then turn out, wrap tightly in greaseproof paper, and store in a tin. This is the start of the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "parkin cure",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yjbvk00001kv477pw679a"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". Do not eat it for at least 3 days. Cut into squares when ready.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
